UIC Alumni Association


Alumni Exchange






Alumni Exchange



UIC is at the forefront of the most pressing issues affecting our city and our rapidly changing world. Our alumni, faculty and students fight disease and injustice, educate leaders, serve and care for our most vulnerable and contribute to our vibrant culture. Amazing things happen when we learn together and share ideas.
Alumni Exchange is a new virtual event series that brings news, knowledge and entertainment to help you learn, grow, explore, connect and even escape from the everyday with a community of UIC alumni and faculty. Join us online.





            Upcoming
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Long COVID: What We’ve Learned
                    

                Join College of Medicine doctors Jerry Krishnan, associate vice chancellor for population health and Bellur Prabhakar, professor of microbiology and immunology, to discuss how far we've come, what we know now and what we're still facing.
            












